# Workspace Context

This repo is an Nx monorepo for `nestjs-live-configs`, a split NestJS live-configuration library.

Key packages:
- `packages/core`: `LiveConfigModule`, `LiveConfigService`, `LiveConfigRef`, shared contracts, and adapter helpers
- `packages/adapter-redis`, `packages/adapter-postgres`, `packages/adapter-sqlite`, `packages/adapter-mongo`: backend-specific store and sync bundles
- `examples/demo-app`: local-only demo app for exercising runtime config reads and updates

Core design rules:
- Consumers should read config through `LiveConfigService` or `LiveConfigRef`, not inject primitive values at boot time.
- Keep backend-specific runtime dependencies out of `packages/core`.
- Preserve the split between store adapters and sync adapters.
- Prefer pub/sub or push-style sync when the backend supports it; use polling as the fallback.

Useful references:
- `README.md`: user-facing overview, installation, backend selection, and quick start
- `.cursor/skills.md`: repo commands, implementation habits, and shared guidance
- `.cursor/skills/`: task-specific skills for adapters, validation, and release work
- `examples/demo-app`: demo app uses Nest CLI `start`, `start:dev`, and `build` scripts, prebuilds local package dependencies, and exposes Swagger at `/docs`

Common validation:
- `npm run lint`
- `npm run typecheck`
- `npm test`
- `npm run build`
- `docker compose up -d` for local databases

Maintenance:
- If you change package layout, supported backends, important workflows, commands, or conventions, update this file in the same task.
- Keep this file short, current, and practical; replace stale guidance instead of only appending new notes.
